==English==
===Proverb===
'''a [[friend]] [[in]] [[need]] [[is]] a friend [[indeed]].
#Someone who helps you when you are in need, is a real friend.
#Someone who needs your help will be especially friendly in order to obtain it.

===Usage note===
The first interpretation appears to be the most widely used.

